routes are installed in FIB (B>* entries).\n\n3) Anomaly Detection and Localization\n- No data-plane outage detected: end-to-end reachability is normal, no packet loss observed, and RTTs are consistent with expectations for a small lab fabric.\n- Control-plane inconsistencies observed:\n  - Uneven prefix counts from neighbors:\n    - spine_router_0_0 receives fewer prefixes (24) from each super-spine neighbor, whereas spine_router_0_1 receives 32 from each super-spine neighbor.\n    - spine_router_0_0 sees only 1 or 4 PfxRcd from certain leaf neighbors, while spine_router_0_1 sees 32 from each leaf neighbor.\n  - These differences indicate asymmetric route propagation or policy filtering between super_spine_router_0 and spine_router_0_0 (or differing import/export policies on spine_router_0_0 vs spine_router_0_1).\n  - Despite these differences, route coverage in the FIB on both spines appears complete for the tested subnets (data-plane unaffected).\n- CLI discrepancy:\n  - On spine_router_0_1, “show bgp ipv4 unicast 10.0.0.0/24” returned “Network not in table,” while the route table shows B>* 10.0.0.0/24 present via super-spine peers. This is likely a transient or command lookup quirk; not corroborated as a persistent control-plane fault.\n\n4) Root Cause Assessment (for identified abnormalities)\n- The asymmetric BGP prefix counts likely stem from differences in BGP advertisement/acceptance policies or route propagation behavior on:\n  - super_spine_router_0 toward spine_router_0_0, and/or\n  - spine_router_0_0’s import filtering compared to spine_router_0_1.\n- Leaves appear to (re)advertise more than only their local /24 to spines (e.g., PfxRcd 32 on spine_router_0_1 from a single leaf peer). This behavior is permitted by “no bgp ebgp-requires-policy” and suggests no export filtering, which is atypical in some Clos designs that restrict leaf advertisements. It explains high PfxRcd counts but is not currently causing reachability issues.\n\nSummary\n- Network health: Data-plane is healthy with full reachability across tested prefixes and no loss.\n- Abnormalities: Inconsistent BGP prefix counts between super-spine/spines and leaves/spines, suggesting non-uniform route propagation or policies. No immediate data-plane impact observed.\n- Fault localization: If action were needed, investigation would focus on BGP policy/advertisement differences on super_spine_router_0 and spine_router_0_0 (compared to spine_router_0_1).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 25024, "output_tokens": 5321, "total_tokens": 30345, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 24960}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4096}}}
